# ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬ STEP 3b: Vanity creator-store slugs (the actual fix) ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬ГўвЂќв‚¬
#
# uyehtech.com/marketplace/uyeh-store  ГўвЂ вЂ™  serves /marketplace/creator-store.html
#        ГўвЂ вЂ™ creator-store.html reads the slug from the URL path itself
#          (resolveSlug() falls back to the last path segment when there's
#          no ?store=/?slug= param Гўв‚¬вЂќ see creator-store.html line ~1735)
#
# MUST come after every specific rule above (Steps 1 & 3) Гўв‚¬вЂќ first match
# wins, so /marketplace/login etc. will always match their own exact rule
# first and never fall through to this catch-all.
#
# Trade-off, accepted: a mistyped /marketplace/whatever with no matching
# store will match this rule and load creator-store.html, which then shows
# its own "Store not found" error state (showError()) rather than a real
# Netlify 404. That's a deliberate choice to support clean vanity links Гўв‚¬вЂќ
# not a bug, but worth knowing if you're ever debugging a "wrong" 404.

/marketplace/:storeSlug            /marketplace/creator-store.html    200

